 the dipole operator to the 
Standard Model Lagrangian. In the
notation of Kuno  and Okada\cite{KunoOkada}

text:
\begin{equation}
\begin{array}{c|ccc}
{\rm Model ~type} &\rho^U  & \rho^D  & \rho^E  \\
\hline
{\rm Type ~I}  &Y^U {\cot\beta} & - Y^D{\tan\beta} & -Y^E {\tan\beta}\\
{\rm Type ~II} &-Y^U {\tan\beta} & - Y^D{\tan\beta} & -Y^E {\tan\beta} \\
